  An instrument has to feel instant. When you tap between pages in a music controller, the new page should already be there — not mount in front of you. Knobbler's page switches used to sit on a uniform ~700ms floor, and the fix was a chain of four React Native lessons: stop unmounting pages, keep hot state out of the broad context, freeze off-screen work, and window the heavy grid. Here's the saga, with before/after numbers on a fast tablet and a slow one.
